        "content": {
          "Prompt": {
            "prompt": "I think the default should be 1 Internal, this can be freely used with th eexisting cahnnels but not with A2A for example or over the internet"
          }
        },
        "timestamp": "2026-03-20T01:41:28.759197328+01:00",
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "c57496a2-8c18-4623-b9aa-579b8502cb8f",
          "content": "It's already 1 (internal) as the default — both in the schema (`classification INTEGER DEFAULT 1`) and in `instantStore` (`params.classification ?? 1`). So existing memories and any new ones without explicit classification are internal by default.\n\nYour point about A2A is good though — when the agent surfaces memories through A2A or any external channel, it should respect `maxClassification=0` (public only), same as group chats. That's a recall-time concern — the agent just needs to pass `--max-classification 0` when recalling for A2A contexts. The classification skill already says group chats = public only, but I can make A2A explicit. Want me to add that to the skill doc?"
        }
      },
