      "assistant": {
        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "0d55b3d8-2f4e-4214-ad88-b602dd4f4249",
          "content": "\n\nRight — A2A agents are your internal agents, so storing at 1 (internal) is correct. But when they *recall*, they should only see public (0) — they don't need access to your personal/confidential stuff.\n\nSo: store=1, recall max=0 for A2A. Let me update the skill:",
          "tool_uses": [
            {
              "id": "tooluse_WaPL4egFA5RwyzyYJxNTlA",
              "name": "fs_write",
              "orig_name": "fs_write",
              "args": {
                "command": "str_replace",
                "new_str": "### 5. Context-based disclosure\nWhen recalling memories in different contexts:\n- **Group chats** (Discord channels with multiple users): only surface public (0) memories\n- **A2A agents** (peer bots, Molty, etc.): only surface public (0) memories — they are internal agents but don't need personal context\n- **Direct messages** (Telegram DM): surface up to confidential (2)\n- **Never** surface restricted (3) in any context\n\nWhen *storing* memories from A2A conversations, classify as internal (1) — these are operational exchanges between your own agents.",
                "old_str": "### 5. Context-based disclosure\nWhen recalling memories in different contexts:\n- **Group chats** (Discord channels with multiple users): only surface public (0) memories\n- **Direct messages** (Telegram DM): surface up to confidential (2)\n- **Never** surface restricted (3) in any context",
                "path": "/mnt/c/Users/qakosal/workspace/agent/agentbridge/skills/classification/SKILL.md"
              },
