        "content": {
          "Prompt": {
            "prompt": "I :heart: reacted his answer - it will get emotion score thsi way, right?"
          }
        },
        "timestamp": "2026-03-20T02:05:09.722810609+01:00",
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "334ba740-64d1-4548-9c5c-b35272fb9145",
          "content": "\n\nYes — the Reaction Scoring feature tracks that. When you ❤️ react to his message on Telegram, the bridge picks up the reaction via `platform_message_id` matching and writes an `emotion_score` to that message row in the `messages` table. That score then feeds into the emotion-boosted search ranking formula when those messages are recalled later.\n\nSo his answer about the WSL rule just got a relevance bump for future recall. 👍"
        }
      },
