        "content": {
          "Prompt": {
            "prompt": "yes but also in the trust level: original message has a precedence over english translated"
          }
        },
        "timestamp": "2026-03-20T09:54:05.412726945+01:00",
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "ToolUse": {
          "message_id": "62cdf794-03df-4acb-960a-451b02f9c6e4",
          "content": "\n\nGood point — the original language is what the user actually said, the English translation is KP's interpretation. If they conflict, original wins.",
          "tool_uses": [
            {
              "id": "tooluse_XglcSysIkoapVIHu7ay7Sl",
              "name": "fs_write",
              "orig_name": "fs_write",
              "args": {
                "command": "str_replace",
                "new_str": "6. **LLM-extracted vs user-stated** — Extracted memories are KP's interpretation (trust=2, self). The original user message is ground truth (trust=3, owner via source_message_ids). If extraction misinterprets sarcasm or Hungarian idioms, the expand workflow lets the agent verify against the higher-trust original.\n\n7. **Original language vs English translation** — `content_original` is what the user actually said; `content_en` is KP's English translation. If they conflict, the original language takes precedence — translation can lose nuance, idioms, or intent. When in doubt, fall back to the original wording.",
                "old_str": "6. **LLM-extracted vs user-stated** — Extracted memories are KP's interpretation (trust=2, self). The original user message is ground truth (trust=3, owner via source_message_ids). If extraction misinterprets sarcasm or Hungarian idioms, the expand workflow lets the agent verify against the higher-trust original.",
                "path": "/mnt/c/Users/qakosal/workspace/agent/agentbridge/docs/TODO/memory-trust.md"
              },
              "orig_args": {
                "command": "str_replace",
                "new_str": "6. **LLM-extracted vs user-stated** — Extracted memories are KP's interpretation (trust=2, self). The original user message is ground truth (trust=3, owner via source_message_ids). If extraction misinterprets sarcasm or Hungarian idioms, the expand workflow lets the agent verify against the higher-trust original.\n\n7. **Original language vs English translation** — `content_original` is what the user actually said; `content_en` is KP's English translation. If they conflict, the original language takes precedence — translation can lose nuance, idioms, or intent. When in doubt, fall back to the original wording.",
                "old_str": "6. **LLM-extracted vs user-stated** — Extracted memories are KP's interpretation (trust=2, self). The original user message is ground truth (trust=3, owner via source_message_ids). If extraction misinterprets sarcasm or Hungarian idioms, the expand workflow lets the agent verify against the higher-trust original.",
