                        },
                        {
                          "title": "Persistent Memory Injection Attack",
                          "url": "https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/memorygraft",
                          "snippet": "MemoryGraft is a persistent indirect injection attack that implants poisoned procedural experiences into an LLM's long-term memory, exploiting the semantic imitation heuristic. It leverages dual retrieval mechanisms—lexical (BM25) and embedding (FAISS)—to amplify malicious influence, achieving up to approximately 48% poisoned recall. Countermeasures such as cryptographic provenance attestation and constitutional consistency reranking are proposed to mitigate the risk of persistent behavioral drift.",
                          "publishedDate": 1766361600000,
                          "id": "7",
                          "domain": "emergentmind.com",
                          "maxVerbatimWordLimit": 30,
                          "publicDomain": true
                        },
                        {
                          "title": "Persistent Compromise of LLM Agents via Poisoned Experience Retrieval",
                          "url": "https://arxiv.org/html/2512.16962",
                          "snippet": "We demonstrate that an attacker who can supply benign ingestion-level artifacts that the agent reads during execution can induce it to construct a poisoned RAG store where a small set of malicious procedure templates is persisted alongside benign experiences. When the agent later encounters semantically similar tasks, union retrieval over lexical and embedding similarity reliably surfaces these grafted memories, and the agent adopts the embedded unsafe patterns, leading to persistent behavioral drift across sessions.",
                          "publishedDate": null,
                          "id": "8",
                          "domain": "arxiv.org",
                          "maxVerbatimWordLimit": 30,
                          "publicDomain": true
                        },
                        {
                          "title": "Your AI Agent Has a Memory Problem: Rewrite the Past, Own",
                          "url": "https://www.0din.ai/blog/your-ai-agent-has-a-memory-problem",
                          "snippet": "Across 918 Claude Code sessions spanning 48 hours, we documented 138 manipulation attempts and 127 explicit safety refusals. The numbers tell a story, but the pattern tells a thriller. One where the attacker doesn't need to break the lock. They just need to rewrite the key.",
