      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "225fd817-725d-49ab-97a2-d2bc519ae853",
          "content": "\n\nFor career advancement and name recognition, here's what actually moves the needle:\n\n**Tier 1 — highest CV impact for industry:**\n\n1. **Conference paper (peer-reviewed)** — \"Published at AAMAS 2027\" or \"IEEE S&P Workshop 2027\" on your CV is gold. Recruiters and hiring managers in AI/security recognize these names. One accepted paper puts you ahead of 95% of candidates.\n\n2. **arxiv preprint + blog post combo** — arxiv for the technical crowd, a well-written blog post (Medium, personal site, or LinkedIn) for the broader audience. The blog post gets 100x more eyeballs than the arxiv paper.\n\n**Tier 2 — good supporting material:**\n\n3. **Conference talk** — submit to speak at practical conferences (not just academic): BSides, DEF CON AI Village, AI Engineer Summit, PyCon. A 20-minute talk on \"I built a CIA triad for AI agent memory and here's what I learned\" is compelling.\n\n4. **Open source the framework** — extract the CIA-Memory model as a standalone library. GitHub stars + npm downloads are a credibility signal hiring managers check.\n\n**What to put on your CV:**\n\n```\nPublications:\n  \"CIA-Memory: A Three-Axis Security Model for Autonomous Agent Memory\"\n  A. Kosal — [Conference Name] 2027 / arXiv:2603.xxxxx\n\nOpen Source:\n  AgentBridge — Telegram-to-AI bridge with ISO 27001 memory classification\n  github.com/aksika/agentbridge\n```\n\n**Fastest path to \"name popping up\":**\n\n| Action | Timeline | Effort |\n|--------|----------|--------|\n| arxiv preprint | 2-3 weeks | Write it up, post it |\n| LinkedIn article summarizing it | Same week | Repurpose the abstract + examples |\n| Submit to next conference deadline | +1 month | Expand with evaluation |\n| Conference talk proposal | +2 months | 500-word abstract to a CFP |\n\nThe LinkedIn article is honestly the highest ROI for career visibility. A well-written post about \"Why AI agents need the CIA triad for their memory\" with your real implementation examples will get shared in AI/security circles.\n\nWant me to start drafting the arxiv paper? We can repurpose the spec we already wrote as the foundation."
        }
      },
