    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "Here's the situation:\n\n- The bridge process is running (pid 1330047, `node dist/main.js --web --agent`, started at 22:56 on pts/14)\n- No stuck `agentbridge-sleep` processes — the old ones were killed earlier ✅\n- The kiro-cli in the `kiro-bridge` tmux session is idle at the prompt — no active work being sent to it\n- Last sleep audit completed at 22:59 successfully\n- Last log entry was at 22:27 (a heartbeat tick that skipped sleep-trigger because transport was busy)\n- The bridge log file hasn't been written to in ~1 hour despite `LOG_LEVEL=debug`\n- Memory DB was last active at 23:05\n\nThe bridge appears to be running but quiet — no messages coming in from Telegram, no errors, no sleep processes hanging. It's just sitting there polling with nothing to do. The build we just did hasn't been deployed yet though — the running process is still using the old `dist/` from before our fixes. You'll need to rebuild and restart to pick up the Bug 1 and Bug 2 fixes.\n\nWant me to do a deploy?\n[Tool uses: none]",
