    "The bridge (pid 1330047) has a live `kiro-cli acp --agent professor` child (pid 1330222). It's running fine.\n\nThe last log entry at 22:30 shows a Telegram update came in but the log line is truncated mid-JSON. After that — nothing for an hour despite `LOG_LEVEL=debug`. Either:\n\n1. The logger broke/stopped flushing after that truncated write\n2. The bridge is stuck processing that 22:30 message and never returned to the poll loop\n3. No more Telegram messages came in (but with debug level, heartbeat ticks should still log)\n\nThe heartbeat logged at 22:27 but nothing after 22:30 — no more heartbeat ticks in over an hour. That suggests the bridge is **hung** — likely stuck waiting on the ACP response for that 22:30 message and the heartbeat/event loop is blocked.\n\nWant me to check what the kiro-cli ACP child is doing, or just restart the bridge with the new build?\n[Tool uses: none]",
