    "All 600 tests pass. Here's what's done:\n\n**Task 3.2 — Cron checker:** `src/components/cron-checker.ts`\n- `checkCron()` reads `cron.json`, finds entries where `fireAt <= now` and `fired === false`\n- Reminders → appended to `pending_reminders.json`\n- Tasks → spawns `kiro-cli acp` subprocess, calls `onTaskComplete` callback with result\n\n**Task 3.3 — Pending reminders pickup:** wired in `main.ts`\n- Every 5 min (same as heartbeat), reads `pending_reminders.json`\n- Injects each reminder as a synthetic Telegram update with `[Scheduled reminder]` prefix\n- Clears the file after processing\n- Also runs once on startup to catch overdue entries\n\n**Task 3.4 — Task subagent + TG report:** wired in `main.ts`\n- `onTaskComplete` callback creates a `TelegramApi` instance and sends `✅ Cron task completed: <message>\\n\\n<result>` to the chat\n\n**Cleanup:** `cronInterval` cleared on shutdown.\n\nAll of Job 2 and Job 3 are now complete. Build clean, 600/600 tests pass.\n[Tool uses: none]",
