    "Found it. The bridge is actually alive — it's pid **1335746** now (not 1330047 which was the old one). And the problem is clear:\n\n**pid 1342694** — a bash script that's been running for 12 minutes. It's trying to inject X/Twitter cookies into the Docker-based headed browser via `docker exec agentbridge-browser node inject.mjs`. That `docker exec` (pid 1342710) is **hanging**.\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "Here's the picture:\n\n**`inject.mjs` (pid 111 inside container) has been stuck for 12 minutes.** It's the cookie injection script that:\n1. Navigates to x.com\n2. Tries to import `BrowserManager` from the container's app code to get the session context\n3. Injects cookies\n4. Navigates to x.com/home\n5. Takes a screenshot\n\nIt's hanging on one of those steps — likely the `BrowserManager.getInstance()` / `getSession(\"xcookie\")` call, or the navigation to x.com/home after cookie injection. The headed Chrome (pid 128/1342778) is running but the script never completes.\n\nThe bridge itself (pid 1335746) is alive but blocked because kiro-cli issued that `execute_bash` command and is waiting for it to return.\n\nWant me to kill the stuck `docker exec` and the inject script to unblock KP?\n[Tool uses: none]",
