    "> but wait sorry: 1st how can we avoid the previous hanging bug? I think I wanna redisign the WoW: the main agent ALWAYS should be calling a subagent who does these complex tasks, similarly to the SleepingAgnet, he should be calling the Browsing Agent .. what do you think?",
    "\n[Tool uses: thinking]",
    "100% agree. The root cause is that the professor's ACP session is single-threaded — when it issues an `execute_bash` that hangs, the entire bridge is dead. No messages, no heartbeat, nothing.\n\nThe subagent pattern already works for sleep. Here's how I'd design it for browser:\n\n**Current (broken):**\n```\nUser: \"check my X notifications\"\n  → Professor → execute_bash: docker exec ... node inject.mjs → HANGS 12min → bridge dead\n```\n\n**Proposed:**\n```\nUser: \"check my X notifications\"\n  → Professor → execute_bash: agentbridge-browse --task \"check X notifications\" --chat-id 123\n  → CLI returns immediately: { \"ok\": true, \"taskId\": \"abc\", \"status\": \"spawned\" }\n  → Professor tells user: \"On it, I'll report back shortly\"\n  → Professor is FREE for new messages\n  \n  Background:\n  → Detached kiro-cli acp --agent browser-agent (with browser steering)\n  → Does the work (navigate, screenshot, extract, etc.)\n  → On exit → writes result to pending queue (same pattern as cron reminders)\n  → Bridge picks it up next tick → sends to chat\n```\n\nThe pieces:\n\n1. `agentbridge-browse` CLI — thin launcher, spawns detached subprocess, returns immediately\n2. `browser-agent` persona — kiro-cli agent with browser-specific steering (knows about docker exec, IPC socket, cookie injection, etc.)\n3. Result delivery — reuse `pending_reminders.json` or a dedicated `pending_results.json`\n4. Timeout — the CLI could also spawn a watchdog that kills the browser-agent after N minutes (prevents the infinite hang)\n\nThis matches the existing patterns:\n- Sleep → `agentbridge-sleep` spawns detached, bridge queues messages, reports when done\n- Cron tasks → spawn kiro-cli, report via TG on exit\n- Browser → same pattern, spawn browser-agent, report via pending queue\n\nThe skill steering for professor would say \"for any browser task, call `agentbridge-browse` — never run browser commands directly.\"\n\nWant me to build it?\n[Tool uses: none]",
