    "Here's the situation:\n\n**The sleep at 00:47 was harmless** — it ran a clean cycle, found the daily summary already existed, skipped everything, zero changes. No data corruption or duplicate work.\n\n**BUT the sleep process is still hanging** (pid 1451674, spawned 00:46, still alive). This is Bug 1 again — the `process.exit(0)` fix is in your source code but the bridge hasn't been redeployed yet. The running bridge is still using old `dist/` without the fix.\n\n**You also have 9 orphaned kiro-cli processes** from previous sessions that never exited:\n- 2 from Mar 13 (3 days ago!)\n- 7 from Mar 15 (old bridge)\n\nWant me to:\n1. Kill all the orphans + the hanging sleep process\n2. Rebuild and redeploy so the fix actually takes effect\n\n```bash\n# This would clean up everything\nkill 292334 404374 985952 1118037 1120585 1121074 1297104 1330280 1335979 1451674\n```\n\nThe root cause of \"multiple sleep problems\" is exactly this — every bridge restart triggers a sleep, and without the `process.exit(0)` fix deployed, each one stays alive forever accumulating zombie ACP sessions.\n[Tool uses: none]",
