    "\n[Tool uses: fs_write]",
    "All done. Here's the summary:\n\n**Intelligent Cron** — `checkMissedCrons()` in `cron-checker.ts`:\n- On startup (`catchUp=true`): parses `crontab -l`, finds `# agentbridge-managed` entries, checks if any should have fired since last tracked run. If missed → executes immediately.\n- On 5-min interval (`catchUp=false`): just updates `cron_runs.json` tracking so next startup knows what was covered.\n- Tracking file: `~/.agentbridge/memory/cron_runs.json`\n\n**Flow:** Bridge down at 8am → cron misses → bridge starts at 10am → `checkMissedCrons(true)` sees the 8am job was missed → fires it → Brownie does the AI news scan → result delivered to chat.\n\n**Tests:** 5 new tests (no crontab, untagged entries, catch-up execution, track-only mode, skip when recent). 62 files, 638 tests, all passing.\n\n**Cron skill updated** with `# agentbridge-managed` tag requirement and catch-up docs.\n[Tool uses: none]",
