    "Done. Saved to `.kiro/steering/feature-update-workflow.md` with `alwaysApply: true` so it's active on every conversation. \n\nThe key lessons baked in from today's sleep debugging:\n- **§1** — Two `SleepTrigger` instances with unshared state (the actual bug)\n- **§3** — Refactor duplicates first, then fix once (what we did: shared instance)\n- **§4** — Stale test said \"always returns true\" while code had conditions (caught and rewritten)\n- **§5** — Bridge was running old dist without the fix (wasted debugging time)\n- **§6** — 9 orphaned kiro-cli processes from pre-fix runs\n- **§7** — `stdio: \"ignore\"` hid why 4 sleep spawns crashed silently\n[Tool uses: none]",
