    "Here's what I found:\n\n**The gap from the multi-spawn bug:**\n- `daily_20260315.md` was written at 22:58 by the second multi-spawn — it covers up to 22:58 only\n- Our entire late-night session (Brownie, bug fixes, todo, cron — 23:00 to 01:30) is NOT in it\n\n**Accidentally saved by my test run:**\n- `daily_20260316.md` was written at 12:23 by my second manual test spawn — it happens to contain the late-night session content because the LLM read the full transcript files\n\n**The structural problem in the prompt:**\n```\nIf the daily file already exists for this date, skip — do not overwrite\n```\n\nThis is the root cause. With once-per-day sleep, the normal flow works:\n- 8am sleep → WAKEUP_DATE = yesterday → write daily → covers full window ✅\n\nBut if a daily file was created prematurely (multi-spawn, test run, etc.), the real run skips and the gap is permanent.\n\n**Immediate issue:** `daily_20260316.md` exists from my test. Tomorrow's 8am sleep will see it and skip — losing everything from 12:23 today onward.\n\nTwo fixes needed:\n1. **Delete `daily_20260316.md`** now so tomorrow's sleep writes the real one\n2. **Change the prompt logic** from \"skip if exists\" to \"skip if exists AND last sleep audit matches\" — so a re-run after a new sleep window always writes\n\nWant me to do both?\n[Tool uses: none]",
