    "Good idea, but we need to be selective — there's secrets and binary data in there. I'd init a separate repo in `~/.agentbridge/` with a strict `.gitignore`. Here's what should and shouldn't be tracked:\n\n**Track:**\n- `.kiro/steering/` — skills, personality\n- `sleeping_prompt.md`, `browsing_prompt.md` — prompt templates\n- `memory/daily/`, `memory/weekly/`, `memory/quarterly/` — summaries\n- `memory/audit/` — sleep audits\n- `memory/todo.md`, `memory/cron.json` — user data\n- `research/`, `reports/` — generated content\n- `topics/` — knowledge files\n\n**Don't track:**\n- `.env` — secrets (bot tokens, auth tokens)\n- `titok/` — credentials\n- `memory/memory.db*` — binary DB, changes constantly\n- `memory/pending_*.json` — transient state\n- `logs/` — ephemeral\n- `dist/` — deployed build artifacts\n\nWant me to set it up?\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
