    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "All scripts are covered:\n\n| Script | Source of truth | Tracked in |\n|--------|----------------|------------|\n| `deploy.sh` | `scripts/deploy.sh` | Main project ✅ |\n| `agentbridge.sh` | `scripts/agentbridge.sh` | Main project ✅ |\n| `browser-docker.sh` | `scripts/browser-docker.sh` | Main project ✅ |\n| `tmux-session.sh` | `scripts/tmux-session.sh` | Main project ✅ |\n| SQL/test scripts | `scripts/*.sql`, `scripts/*.sh` | Main project ✅ |\n| CLI wrappers (`agentbridge-*`) | Generated by `deploy.sh` | Neither — regenerated on deploy ✅ |\n| `mcporter` | Separate project | Separate repo |\n\nThe CLI wrappers in `~/.agentbridge/` are just one-line `exec node ...` stubs generated by `deploy.sh`. No need to track them — they're recreated every deploy. That's why we excluded them from the `~/.agentbridge` repo.\n\nEverything's covered. Source in the main project, runtime config in `~/.agentbridge/`.\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> ok, so we pushed the db to the git? I want this to be encrypted with a key which is in the titok folder",
    "\n[Tool uses: thinking]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "`Salted__` — that's openssl encrypted. Working tree has the raw SQLite, git stores the encrypted version.\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "Done. Setup:\n\n- **Key:** `~/.agentbridge/titok/db.key` (AES-256-CBC, chmod 600)\n- **Git filter:** `encrypt-db` clean/smudge — encrypts on commit, decrypts on checkout\n- **Working tree:** raw SQLite (KP reads it normally)\n- **Git objects:** `Salted__...` encrypted blob\n\nTo restore on another machine: put the same `db.key` in `titok/`, clone, and the smudge filter decrypts automatically on checkout.\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> hm, can you explain a bit more about the smuge filter?",
    "\n\nGit filters intercept files as they move between the working tree and the git object store:\n\n```\nWorking tree (raw SQLite)\n    │\n    ▼ git add (CLEAN filter runs)\n    │ → openssl encrypt → stored as encrypted blob in .git/\n    │\n    ▼ git checkout (SMUDGE filter runs)\n    │ → openssl decrypt → raw SQLite back in working tree\n    │\nWorking tree (raw SQLite again)\n```\n\n- **Clean** = \"clean up before storing\" — runs when you `git add` or `git commit`. Takes the raw file, pipes it through `openssl enc`, git stores the encrypted output.\n- **Smudge** = \"smudge/expand when checking out\" — runs when you `git checkout`, `git clone`, or `git pull`. Takes the encrypted blob from git, pipes it through `openssl dec`, puts the decrypted file in your working tree.\n\nSo KP and your code always see the normal SQLite file. Git never stores the plaintext. Anyone who clones the repo without the key in `titok/db.key` gets garbage (the encrypted blob) and the smudge filter fails.\n\nThe `required true` setting means git will error out if the filter fails (e.g., missing key) rather than silently storing/checking out unencrypted data.\n[Tool uses: none]",
