    "I'm a planning agent - I can read and analyze code but not modify it. I can help you plan the implementation instead.\n\nHere's the plan for the rebuild script:\n\n**`src/cli/rebuild-db.ts`** — reads all JSONL transcripts, inserts into `messages` + `chat_backup` tables. FTS triggers auto-index.\n\n**What it restores:**\n- 624 messages (606 from your chat + 18 from Molty) → `messages` + `messages_fts`\n- Same into `chat_backup`\n\n**What it doesn't restore (but will rebuild automatically):**\n- `extracted_memories` — the heartbeat extraction process runs periodically and will re-extract from the messages table. The `extraction_watermarks` table is empty, so it'll process everything from the start.\n\n**Logic:**\n1. Read all `.jsonl` files from `memory/transcripts/*/`\n2. Parse each line: `{role, content, timestamp, chatId, sessionId}`\n3. Sort by timestamp\n4. Insert into `messages` and `chat_backup` in a single transaction\n5. Verify FTS count matches\n\nWant me to switch to execution and build this?\n[Tool uses: none]",
