    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Extracted memories aren't auto-extracted by a batch process. They're created one-by-one when KP calls `agentbridge-store` (the `instant_store` tool) during conversations. KP decides what's worth remembering and stores it in real-time.\n\nSo there's no automatic rebuild. The 120 extracted memories were accumulated over ~2 weeks of conversations as KP chose to store facts, preferences, and events.\n\n**Options to speed up recovery:**\n\n1. **Let it rebuild naturally** — as you chat with KP, it'll store new memories. Slow but organic.\n2. **Ask KP to re-extract** — send KP a message like \"Read through your transcript history and re-extract all important memories using agentbridge-store.\" It has access to the transcripts and the store tool. One conversation could recover most of them.\n3. **Feed the daily summaries** — the dailies contain the distilled facts. Ask KP to read each daily and store the key facts.\n\nOption 2 is fastest — KP could probably re-extract most of the 120 memories in a single session. Want to try that?\n[Tool uses: none]",
