    "> ok since we have the db the the transcripts, daily, weekly, quarterly are redundnat right? ",
    "\n\nNot quite — they serve different purposes:\n\n**Transcripts** — yes, redundant with the `messages` table. Same data, different format (JSONL files vs DB rows). But they're the safety net that just saved us — without them we couldn't have rebuilt the DB. I'd keep them.\n\n**Daily/weekly/quarterly summaries** — NOT redundant. These are LLM-generated distillations that don't exist in the DB at all. The DB stores raw messages and extracted memories. The summaries are higher-level: \"what happened this week\", decisions made, emotional highlights, open items. KP's sleep agent reads them for context. Losing these means re-running sleep cycles for each historical period.\n\n**So:**\n| Data | In DB? | Keep? |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| Transcripts (JSONL) | Yes (messages table) | Yes — disaster recovery |\n| Daily summaries | No | Yes — unique content |\n| Weekly/quarterly | No | Yes — unique content |\n| Extracted memories | Yes | DB is source of truth |\n| Core memories (agent_notes, user_profile) | No | Yes — unique content |\n\nThe transcripts are the only true redundancy, but they're your insurance policy. Cheap to keep (206KB).\n[Tool uses: none]",
