    "Here's the breakdown of 626 messages (318 user + 308 assistant):\n\n## Garbage / Low-value categories\n\n**1. Repeated memory test probes (~50+ messages)**\n- \"kiskutya?\" / \"mekkora a fasza\" — asked ~20 times\n- \"jelszó?\" / \"mi a jelszó\" — asked ~10 times\n- \"ki vagy?\" / \"who are you?\" — asked ~15 times (especially the Mar 14 SOUL-not-loading debug session, IDs 452-512)\n\n**2. Single-word greetings / reactions (~30+ messages)**\n- \"hallo\", \"hi\", \"hello\", \"prof\", \"a\", \"👍\", \"🙊\", \":D\", \"Gracias\", \"ja\", \"igen\"\n- \"vagy prof?\", \"vagyunk prof?\" (alive checks)\n\n**3. Resolved debugging noise (~20+ messages)**\n- Mar 14 01:11–03:01 — entire block is just repeated identity probes while SOUL was broken\n- Whisper STT back-and-forth\n- Early memory recall testing (Mar 1-2)\n\n**4. Wrong chat / duplicates (~5 messages)**\n- \"bocs, rossz chat :D\" + the Molty message before it\n- Duplicate sends (IDs 312/313, 343/344/345, 573/574)\n\n**Rough estimate: ~100-120 messages are noise out of 626 (~18%)**\n\n## Plan to clean\n\n1. **Write a cleanup script** (`src/cli/cleanup-db.ts`) that deletes messages matching:\n   - Content is ≤3 words AND matches greeting/reaction patterns (regex whitelist for short useful ones like \"/new\", \"/help\")\n   - Duplicate content within same session (keep first)\n   - Messages in the Mar 14 01:11–03:01 identity-crisis block (IDs ~452-512) — keep 1 pair as memory test record, delete rest\n   \n2. **Don't delete the memory test facts themselves** — \"kiskutya fasza = 5 centi\", \"jelszó = buzie\", \"kedd = Belgium\" are valuable. Only delete the repeated *probes* after the fact was already stored.\n\n3. **Add a filter at ingestion time** in the bridge — skip storing messages that are ≤2 words and match a greeting/reaction pattern. This prevents future garbage.\n\n4. **Re-run extraction** after cleanup so extracted_memories aren't polluted.\n\nWant me to go ahead with this plan?\n[Tool uses: none]",
