    "Good — so Dreamy has `agentbridge-store` available. Now I see the current sleeping prompt has a **CRITICAL SAFETY RULE** in §3 that says \"DO NOT delete any rows from messages\". \n\nThe plan is: instead of deleting, Dreamy should **garbage-collect by summarizing and then deleting** the noise messages. We need to:\n\n1. Lift the safety rule to allow Dreamy to delete specific garbage patterns\n2. Add a new section to the sleeping prompt with GC instructions\n\nA few questions before I plan this:\n\n[1]: Should Dreamy delete the garbage messages from the DB, or just mark them somehow (e.g. move to `chat_backup` table)?\n- a. **Hard delete** — gone from messages table, FTS triggers clean up automatically\n- b. **Move to chat_backup** — recoverable but still out of active search\n- c. **Other**\n\n[2]: What counts as garbage? My read from the data:\n- Single-word/emoji greetings & reactions (👍, :D, \"hi\", \"hallo\", \"ja\")\n- Repeated memory test probes after the fact is already stored (\"kiskutya?\" asked 20x)\n- Duplicate sends (same content within minutes)\n- Anything else you'd add?\n\n[3]: Should the GC run every sleep cycle, or only when message count exceeds a threshold?\n[Tool uses: none]",
