    "Good. Now for question 2 — you mentioned patterns. And question 3 — every sleep or threshold. Let me refine:\n\n[2]: The garbage patterns I see from the data:\n- a. Single-word/emoji greetings & reactions (\"hi\", \"👍\", \":D\", \"ja\", \"igen\")\n- b. Repeated probes where the answer is already in extracted_memories (\"kiskutya?\" asked 20x)\n- c. Duplicate sends (same content within 2 min)\n- d. \"wrong chat\" messages\n- Anything else, or should Dreamy use judgment beyond these patterns?\n\n[3]: Should GC run every sleep cycle, or only when count exceeds a threshold (e.g. >500 messages)?\n[Tool uses: none]",
