    "Subagent came back fast this time. Let me check its classification:\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "Here's the subagent's GC result:\n\n| | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Pre-sleep messages | 626 |\n| Immediate deletes (dupes) | 18 |\n| Post-delete messages | 608 |\n| Garbage marked (7-day grace) | 39 |\n| After grace period expires | 569 |\n| FTS integrity | ✅ |\n\nThe subagent was more conservative than my manual run (39 garbage vs my 104) — it kept things like \"kiskutya?\" repeated probes, emotional reactions, and some filler. That's the \"when in doubt, KEEP\" instruction working.\n\nThe real Dreamy would likely land somewhere in between — it has the full §3 instructions including the repeated-probe rule and emotion harvest steps. Want me to save this diff report?\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> let's think about how we can polish our prompt better",
    "\n[Tool uses: thinking]",
    "Looking at the gaps between my manual pass (104 marked) and the subagent's (39 marked), the prompt needs work in these areas:\n\n**What the subagent missed:**\n\n1. **Repeated probes** — kept all 6x \"kiskutya?\", all 3x \"who are you?\", all 3x \"ki vagy?\". The §3 Step 5 instruction is there but the agent didn't execute it. Needs a concrete SQL query to make it mechanical, not judgment-based.\n\n2. **Whisper/STT garbage** — \"Fønekur og sigtmær\", \"Týžkuťo.\", \"tu dotky mohlti\", \"Cad?\" — garbled transcriptions. Not mentioned in the prompt at all.\n\n3. **Wrong chat** — \"bocs, rossz chat :D\" wasn't caught. Step 2 mentions it but the subagent skipped it entirely.\n\n4. **Emotional reactions** — \"Oh yes!\", \"Good job professor\", \"Gracias\", \"király\" — only partially caught. The emotion harvest concept needs sharper examples.\n\n5. **Filler** — \"Alakulsz akkor tesó\", \"Na nézzük\", \"jaja\", \"you tell me\" — too cautious.\n\n**Proposed prompt improvements:**\n\n- Add a **scan strategy** up front: \"First dump all messages to review, then classify in bulk\" — prevents the agent from getting lost in one-by-one queries\n- Add **whisper/STT garbage** as an explicit category with examples\n- Make Step 5 (repeated probes) **SQL-driven**: give the exact GROUP BY query so it's mechanical\n- Reduce the \"when in doubt, keep\" to \"when in doubt about short messages with no question mark and no instruction verb, mark as garbage\"\n- Add **wrong-chat** detection to Step 2 with explicit patterns\n\nWant me to update the prompt with these refinements, re-run the subagent test, and compare?\n[Tool uses: none]",
