    "> so let's review the tasks and where we are",
    "\n\nHere's where we stand on the Sleep GC plan:\n\n**Task 1: Fix rebuild-db.ts emoji stripping + empty content guard** ✅\n- `rebuild-db.ts` applies `stripEmojis()` before insert\n- `recordMessage()` skips empty content after strip\n- Unit test added and passing (643 total)\n\n**Task 2: Update sleeping prompt §3 with GC instructions** ✅\n- Step 1: Purge expired garbage (>7 days)\n- Step 2: Immediate deletes (dupes, wrong chat, STT garbage)\n- Step 3: Emotion harvest → update score → garbage mark\n- Step 4: Pure noise → garbage mark\n- Step 5: Repeated probes → keep first, garbage mark rest\n- Step 6: Verify extractions → extract missing facts → garbage mark verbose originals\n- Step 7: Report\n- Deployed to `~/.agentbridge/sleeping_prompt.md`\n\n**Task 3: Integration test** ✅\n- `scripts/test-sleep-gc.sh` works (pre-snapshot, diff)\n- Subagent test ran Steps 1-5: 29 immediate deletes, 95 garbage-marked, FTS intact\n- Subagent test ran Step 6 (old compaction version): proved the concept works\n- Step 6 (new verify-extract-mark version): not yet tested with subagent\n\n**Task 4: Deploy and verify** ⏳\n- Prompt deployed ✅\n- `garbage.json` in `.gitignore` ✅\n- As-built docs updated ✅\n- Committed to main repo ✅\n- Sleep trigger tests — not updated yet (plan said \"update sleep-trigger unit tests to reflect GC is part of every sleep cycle\")\n\n**Open items:**\n1. Run subagent integration test with the final Step 6 (verify-extract-mark)\n2. Update sleep-trigger tests if needed\n3. Full test suite run to confirm nothing broke\n\nWant me to run the final integration test with the complete 7-step prompt?\n[Tool uses: none]",
