    "\n[Tool uses: execute_bash]",
    "The last log entry is at `22:39:00` — KP ran `agentbridge-browse --task \"$(cat /home/qakosal/research/AI-news-24h.md)\"`. That `$(cat ...)` expands the entire research prompt file as the `--task` argument. If that file is large, it could have caused the bridge process to hang or crash (massive argument to spawn).\n\nAfter that — nothing. No more log entries. The bridge died silently at 22:39. No \"Bridge starting\" after that, so it was never restarted.\n\nThe likely cause: KP's shell command expanded a large file into a command-line argument, which either crashed the bridge's ACP tool handler or caused the spawned process to hang and block the event loop. Deploy and restart to get back online.\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> what is the max size what he can send back? Make sure that we write the research to the disk (i think we do) and then the agent just sends back a summary - also agentbridge is cutting off the excess as a defense in depth measure. Make this robust!",
    "\n[Tool uses: thinking]",
