    "Now I see the full picture:\n\n**The daily/weekly/quarterly `.md` files are written by kiro during the sleep cycle (§1 of `sleeping_prompt.md`), but they're just files on disk — they're never indexed into the `compactions` table and never searched by the recall pipeline.**\n\nThe `compactions` table exists in the schema but has zero rows (no INSERT code in the codebase). L3 search queries it but always gets nothing.\n\nSo there are two gaps:\n\n1. **The .md consolidation files are orphaned** — kiro writes them, nobody reads them during recall\n2. **The `compactions` table is empty** — the schema exists, L3 search queries it, but nothing populates it\n\nThe fix would be: after kiro writes a daily/weekly/quarterly `.md` file during sleep, **ingest it into the `compactions` table** so L3 search can find it. This could be:\n- A post-sleep hook in `agentbridge-sleep.ts` that scans `~/.agentbridge/memory/{daily,weekly,quarterly}/` and upserts new `.md` files into `compactions`\n- Or an `agentbridge-store --tier daily --file-path ...` CLI extension\n\nThis is actually a bigger deal than I initially thought — it means the entire consolidation layer is write-only. Want me to add this as a new high-priority task in the LCM enhancements plan?\n[Tool uses: none]",
