    "\n\nYes — the context summary at the top of each turn carries forward everything. After `/compact` I'll have:\n\n- All commits made today (up to `ab64559`)\n- The Memory Darwinism plan with your 4 `??` comments\n- We're reviewing them 1-by-1, next up:\n  1. ~~§2-§5 order~~ — done\n  2. **Core knowledge promotion** — \"doesn't it increase dead weight if loaded into every context?\"\n  3. **60+ days archival** — archive DB as additional search layer?\n  4. **Episodic → semantic promotion** — \"explain this\"\n- Unpushed commits waiting for full test + push\n\nGo ahead and `/compact`.\n[Tool uses: none]",
