    "\n[Tool uses: thinking]",
    "`??` #3 — the archive DB idea:\n\n> \"should we have an archive database, and search there as an additional layer?\"\n\nI'd say: **not worth it right now, save as a future idea.**\n\nWhy:\n- FTS5 is fast even with thousands of rows — a separate DB doesn't buy speed\n- The search ranking boost already deprioritizes old/unused memories naturally (low recall_count, stale last_recalled_at)\n- Adding another SQLite file + another search stage = more code to maintain for marginal benefit\n- Edge case problem: a memory about \"user's birthday\" goes 11 months without recall — archiving it would be wrong\n\nWhat \"archival\" should mean today: the fitness review just **deletes** truly dead memories (zero recall, 60+ days, low confidence). They're not worth keeping anywhere — the original raw messages still exist in JSONL transcripts if you ever need forensics.\n\nIf the DB grows to 10K+ extracted memories and search gets noticeably slower, *then* an archive layer makes sense. But that's a scale problem we don't have yet.\n\nWant me to add a one-liner to a future ideas doc instead of a full plan? Or just drop it?\n[Tool uses: none]",
