    "Done (`a24b7ab`). Summary of changes:\n\n**Darwinism plan** (now the single source of truth):\n- Absorbed LCM's `source_message_ids` + `--source-ids` + `agentbridge-expand` into Stage 1\n- Absorbed LCM's consolidation source linking into Stage 4 §2-§5\n- Dropped Stage 5 (episodic→semantic, tasks 17-18)\n- All 4 `??` comments resolved and removed\n- Added Task 16 (core knowledge maintenance ≤10 lines)\n- Renumbered: 18 tasks → 18 tasks (cleaner grouping)\n\n**LCM plan** (now just a reference):\n- Stages 2+3 marked ✅ DONE\n- Stage 5 marked ❌ DROPPED\n- Remaining tasks point to Darwinism as the merge target\n\n**Memory.asbuilt**: Future Ideas section with archive DB one-liner\n\nReady to discuss anything else or start implementing Stage 1?\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> do we need to discuss anything else? ",
    "\n\nAll `??` comments are resolved. The plans are merged and clean.\n\nUnpushed commits waiting:\n- `db8c1ed` docs: add Memory Darwinism plan\n- `0d39c9c` docs: update Memory Darwinism — sleep-batched feedback, confidence field, search ranking boost\n- `2c824f7` docs: update Memory.asbuilt with Darwinism sleep cycle + sleep retry\n- `ab64559` docs: update Memory.asbuilt — remove compactions table refs, add consolidation-search, bootstrap drift check\n- `a24b7ab` docs: merge LCM+Darwinism overlaps, mark completed stages, drop episodic promotion\n\nThese are all docs-only — no code changes, no tests needed. Safe to push whenever you want.\n\nAfter that, next real work is implementing Darwinism Stage 1 (tasks 1-6).\n[Tool uses: none]",
    "> push. And pull up from memory.asbuilt of the recall phases",
