    "Pushed. Now the recall phases from the asbuilt:\n[Tool uses: grep]",
    "\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
    "Here's the current recall cascade (agentbridge-recall, 8 stages):\n\n1. FTS5 full-text on `messages`\n2. Relaxed FTS5 (OR-style, drops tokens < 3 chars)\n3. Substring LIKE (accent-insensitive)\n4. Original-language substring\n5. Extracted memories — English FTS5\n6. Extracted memories — original language FTS5\n7. Consolidation file keyword search\n8. chat_backup LIKE fallback (immutable safety table)\n\nNote: the asbuilt still says \"8-stage\" in two places (lines 188 and 311) but we removed the compactions stage and it should be 8 stages now (consolidation file search replaced compactions). The count is actually still correct — just the label on line 311 says \"8-stage cascade\" which matches.\n\nDarwinism Stage 1 wires recall tracking into stages 5+6 (extracted memories searches) — after those return results, we UPDATE `recall_count` + `last_recalled_at` on each hit. Stage 2 then modifies the ORDER BY in those same queries to boost high-recall results.\n[Tool uses: none]",
