    "> but wait, does it have any overhead cost to implement the message ID (i guess it is marking where it is coming from) ",
    "\n\nZero overhead — the column already exists and `--source-ids` is already wired. The only cost is the sleep agent actually passing it when it calls `agentbridge-store`, which is just adding `--source-ids \"451,452,453\"` to the command.\n\nThe question is: does it add value over `source_timestamp`?\n\n- `source_timestamp` → \"this fact was extracted around 14:32:05\" → query messages ±5 seconds → usually works, but could grab unrelated messages in a fast conversation\n- `source_message_ids` → \"this fact came from messages 451, 452, 453\" → exact, no ambiguity\n\nIt's a precision thing. For expand, timestamp-range is good enough. But for the §1 Feedback Pass, knowing *exactly* which messages a memory came from makes the boost/demote judgment more accurate.\n\nSince the plumbing is already done (column + flag), the only missing piece is Task 12 — the sleep prompt already tells the agent to use `--source-ids` in GC Step 6. So it's actually already fully wired. The sleep agent just needs to follow the instructions.\n\nNothing to implement — it's already there.\n[Tool uses: none]",
