    "> New feature: memory confidentiality.  Az otlet az hogy legyen egy mezo a dbaseben ahova az agent osztalyozza a conf settingjet a memorianak: 4 classification, like in the information systems: open, internal, confidental, secret - research what military use",
    "\n[Tool uses: web_search]",
    "Here's what I found:\n\nThe US military/DoD uses these hierarchical levels (content rephrased for compliance):\n\n| Level | Military | Unauthorized disclosure impact |\n|-------|----------|-------------------------------|\n| 1 | **Unclassified** | No damage to national security |\n| 2 | **Confidential** | Could cause *damage* |\n| 3 | **Secret** | Could cause *serious damage* |\n| 4 | **Top Secret** | Could cause *exceptionally grave damage* |\n\nSome systems also include **Restricted** between Unclassified and Confidential (NATO uses this).\n\nCorporate/ISO 27001 typically uses a similar 4-tier model: Public → Internal → Confidential → Restricted/Secret.\n\nFor your memory system, mapping to your use case:\n\n| Level | Label | Meaning for agentbridge |\n|-------|-------|------------------------|\n| 0 | `open` | Safe to surface anywhere (general facts, preferences) |\n| 1 | `internal` | Normal operational memories (default) |\n| 2 | `confidential` | Sensitive personal info (health, finances, relationships) |\n| 3 | `secret` | Credentials, tokens, security-critical info — never surface in group chats |\n\nThe agent would classify at store time, and recall would filter based on context (e.g., group Discord chat only sees `open`, direct Telegram sees up to `confidential`, sleep agent sees everything).\n\nWant me to build this? The implementation would be:\n- 1 new column `classification INTEGER DEFAULT 1` on `extracted_memories`\n- `--classification` flag on agentbridge-store\n- Recall filtering based on a `--max-classification` param\n- Test\n\nReferences:\n[1] Military Data Classification Levels - https://www.deasylabs.com/post/military-data-classification-levels-a-detailed-examination/\n[2] Classified information - https://www.wikiwand.com/en/articles/Information_classification\n[Tool uses: none]",
