    "> I :heart: reacted his answer - it will get emotion score thsi way, right?",
    "\n\nYes — the Reaction Scoring feature tracks that. When you ❤️ react to his message on Telegram, the bridge picks up the reaction via `platform_message_id` matching and writes an `emotion_score` to that message row in the `messages` table. That score then feeds into the emotion-boosted search ranking formula when those messages are recalled later.\n\nSo his answer about the WSL rule just got a relevance bump for future recall. 👍\n[Tool uses: none]",
